transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. This is Jimmy. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Hi, Jimmy. I need to cancel my prescription, please.

Speaker 1: Okay. Let me see if I can help you with that.

Speaker 2: I'm going to try to pull up the information with the phone number that you're calling from.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Is this Jimmy I'm speaking to?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: All right, Jimmy. I do have you up.

Speaker 1: I do see you're getting the Viagra, 100 milligrams.

Speaker 2: It looks like your prescription is given to you once a month.

Speaker 1: Let me go ahead and take care of your request for you first of all.

Speaker 2: Give me one second.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: All right, Jimmy. Thank you for holding.

Speaker 1: I was able to go in there and I stopped those monthly shipments.

Speaker 2: I also stopped the monthly refills that were included with your prescription,

Speaker 1: and I stopped those monthly charges as well.

Speaker 2: So you won't be getting that anymore.

Speaker 1: Let me ask you, how are the pills working for you, the Viagra that you're getting?

Speaker 2: How are they working for you?

Speaker 1: They work good.

Speaker 2: I just don't need that many a month.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I'll just call and order when I need them.

Speaker 1: Let me do this for you, Jimmy, because Viagra actually costs you a lot more doing it that way.

Speaker 2: Rather than just canceling out altogether, what I can do,

Speaker 1: I can just pause you out for like six months.

Speaker 2: That'll give you a chance to get caught up.

Speaker 1: What that'll do, that'll keep you grandfathered in at the price you're paying,

Speaker 2: and you won't have to pay those tariff prices when they kick in because you're already grandfathered in.

Speaker 1: And also, if six months isn't long enough for you, you can always call like you did today

Speaker 2: and say I'm not ready, push me back a few more months so we can do that.

Speaker 1: Or if you need them before then, you can always call and order before then

Speaker 2: and get them with no problem because you're already grandfathered in with the prescription.

Speaker 1: Is that something I can do for you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, that'll work.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Okay, I'm going to do that.

Speaker 1: Let me give you the date so you know as far as that's concerned.

Speaker 2: The date that I'm going to have looks like the next one would be July the 28th.

Speaker 1: So, like I said, again, if you need them before then, just give us a call and you can get them.

Speaker 2: If you need us to push you back, just give us a call and say push you back a few more months,

Speaker 1: and we'd be more than happy to do that for you.

Speaker 2: Oh, I appreciate it, brother.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much.

Speaker 2: All right, not a problem.

Speaker 1: Consider it done.

Speaker 2: You have a wonderful day.

Speaker 1: All right, thank you, too.

Speaker 2: All right, take care.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
